  "text": ", give a good measure of comparability for fluxes. Difference of mean friction velocities between the towers was less than 5%. There are dips in wind speed in early morning between 600 and 800 h, immediately before flushing-out of CO 2 -enriched air happens, as will be shown below. Wind roses for daytime and nighttime indicated that east is the predominant wind direction during the day, although all directions do occur (wind roses not shown here). There is little difference between the daytime and nighttime wind roses except for a slight increase in the proportion of northerly and southeasterly wind during the night and a reduction in the frequency of the strongest winds. Southerly winds, which could carry pollution from the city of Manaus to the site [CITATION_1] , are among the least common wind directions.",
